    <title>Chicken Biryani</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1>Chicken Biryani Recipe</h1>
            <p>1. Wash the rice and soak it in water for 30 minutes.
            2. Heat oil in a pan. Fry onions until golden brown. Remove half for garnish.
            3. Add ginger-garlic paste to the pan and sauté for 1 minute.
            4. Add chicken pieces, salt, turmeric, red chili powder, and biryani masala. Cook until chicken is half done.
            5. Add yogurt, chopped tomatoes, green chilies, and half of the chopped coriander & mint. Cook for 5-7 minutes.
            6. Boil 4 cups of water in another pot. Add soaked rice and cook until 70% done. Drain water.
            7. Layer the partially cooked rice over the chicken. Sprinkle fried onions, garam masala, and remaining coriander & mint.
            8. Drizzle ghee on top. Cover tightly and cook on low heat for 20-25 minutes (dum cooking).
            9. Serve hot with raita or salad.
            </p>

                <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
                    <ul>
                            <li>Chicken</li>
                                    <li>Rice</li>
                                            <li>Masalay</li>
                                               <li>     Basmati rice – 2 cups</li>
                                                  <li>    Chicken – 500 g (cut into pieces)</li>
                                                     <li>    Onions – 2 large (thinly sliced)</li>
                                                        <li>    Tomatoes – 2 (chopped)</li>
                                                           <li>    Yogurt – 1/2 cup</li>
                                                              <li>    Ginger-garlic paste – 2 tsp</li>
                                                                 <li>    Green chilies – 3-4 (slit)</li>
                                                                    <li>    Biryani masala – 2 tsp</li>
                                                                       <li>    Red chili powder – 1 tsp</li>
                                                                          <li>    Turmeric powder – 1/2 tsp</li>
                                                                             <li>    Garam masala – 1 tsp</li>
                                                                                <li>    Fresh coriander & mint – a handful (chopped)</li>
                                                                                   <li>    Oil – 4 tbsp</li>
                                                                                      <li>    Ghee – 1 tbsp</li>
                                                                                         <li>    Salt – to taste</li>
                                                                                            <li>    Water – 4 cups</li>
                                                                                                </ul>
                                                                                                    

                                                                                                    </body>
